<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1321,283,470]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,477,283,309]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<typeStatus box="[312,373,283,309]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Type</typeStatus>
locality.
</emphasis>
Northeast Atlantic, between Dakar and 
<collectingCountry box="[949,1086,284,310]" name="Cape Verde" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Cabo Verde</collectingCountry>
Islands. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,439,323,349]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Eyes present. Maxilliped palp with 
<number box="[874,889,324,350]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="4.0">4</number>
articles and longer than outer plate. Gnathopod 
<number box="[401,416,364,390]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1.0">1</number>
propodus oval and anteriorly excavate. Gnathopod 
<number box="[1018,1035,364,390]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0">2</number>
, coxa with anterior margin rounded; ischium subequal to carpus in length. Pereopod 
<number box="[987,1001,404,430]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="3.0">3</number>
basis 
<date box="[1076,1120,404,430]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<number box="[1076,1091,404,430]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0">2</number>
X
</date>
length of propodus. Telson entire, distally truncate.
</paragraph>
